The devastated son of a woman murdered last year told jurors how his mom's body was dragged out of her home - as the court played a surveillance video of her estranged husband pulling a large duffel bag.

Tina Adovasio, 40, a nurse from Bronx, New York, vanished from her home on March 11, 2011 after a spat with her estranged husband Edwin Coello, 38, who is now on trial for her murder.

Coello, a former police officer who had several domestic violence claims reported against him by Ms Adovasio, is accused of strangling her and dumping her body in a wooded area.

