Her eldest son Joseph, 18, testified yesterday as jurors were shown a surveillance video of Coello taking the large bag out of his car, which looked as if it contained a body.

As the video played, he told the court: 'Eddy is walking out of my house with my mom. It's my mom,' according to the New York Post.

He said that he had heard his mother arguing with Coello over the phone earlier in the day and he later came home to find his mother wasn't there.

Joseph Adovasio also testified that his stepfather urged him to protect an alibi as suspicion grew of his alleged role in her murder.

